review_blob:
Pours a steady dark reddish amber. 
Strong notes of citrusy grapefruit. Aftertaste is light and lasting. 
9%abv.

a good dry ale but not as hoppy as i would expect an IPA to be. has a dry fizzy start and finishes with little aftertase making it easy to have another one right after. dark brown cola color. fairly straight ale though

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob:
Barleywine, what do you say. this had a slightly bitter taste from the start but the fruityness peaked out soon after that. Reddish-brown dark mohoganish
color. taste of cherry, wine and citrussy rasberry. 10%abv. Yum
